{"descriptions":[{"id":342,"title":null,"content":"\u003cp\u003eFor the most part these are modal verbs that go between the main verb and the final auxiliary. Examples: ཐུབ་, དགོས་, ཆོག\u003c/p\u003e","source_url":null,"is_primary":false,"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:07:34 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:07:34 UTC","authors":[{"id":"2","fullname":"David Germano"}]},{"id":343,"title":null,"content":"\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThere are about twenty or so \u0026ldquo;secondary\u0026rdquo; verbs that go between the principal and auxiliary verb: Principal Verb + Secondary Verb + Auxiliary.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eMost of these verbs are modal verbs:\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདགོས་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To need,\u0026rdquo; \u0026ldquo;to want,\u0026rdquo; \u0026ldquo;to have to\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཐུབ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To be able\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསྲིད་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To be possible\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཆོག་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To be allowed\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཤེས་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To know\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eནུས་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To dare\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའདོད་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To want,\u0026rdquo; \u0026ldquo;to wish\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསྙིང་འདོད་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To wish\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབསམ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To think\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eརྩིས་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To intend,\u0026rdquo; \u0026ldquo;to plan\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThere are also a number of \u0026ldquo;tense-aspect\u0026rdquo; verbs:\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཚར་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To finish\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབསྡད་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To stay\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eརན་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To be time to\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའགྲོའོ་\u003c/span\u003e (\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eགྲབས་\u003c/span\u003e) \u0026ldquo;To be about to\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཆོག་ཆོག་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To be ready to\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eལོང་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To have the time to\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eDirectional verbs can also function as secondary verbs:\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཡོང་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To come\u0026rdquo; (action toward)\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའགྲོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To go\u0026rdquo; (action away from)\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e","source_url":null,"is_primary":true,"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:07:34 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:07:34 UTC","authors":[{"id":"6","fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre"}]}]}